    <div class="answer" style="display: none;">

      <p>A: Excellent question. Bigger Bird has numerous policies and safeguards to ensure that you
      are protected in the unlikely event that we terminate our operations for any reason.</p>

      <p>The most important piece of the puzzle is prevention. We operate our business very
      conservatively, growing slowly and carefully. True, no one will read about our amazing success
      in the paper, but neither will they read about our extraordinary failure.</p>

      <p>If you ever decide to leave Bigger Bird, whether or not Bigger Bird is still a going
      concern, we will do everything we can to ensure a smooth transition to your next vendor.</p>

      <p>Finally, CEO Aaron Namba is a diehard serial entrepreneur. There have been many ventures
      before Bigger Bird (and many will follow), but Aaron always takes care of his customers. One
      of Bigger Bird's clients actually started out as a client of Aaron Namba Hosting back in 1999.
      Even if something happens to Bigger Bird, you can rest assured that you are in very good
      hands.</p>

    </div>
  </li>
</ul>

